2500|$|The term [...] "Rockefeller Republican" [...] {{was used}} 1960–1980 to {{designate}} a {{faction of the}} party holding [...] "moderate" [...] views {{similar to those of}} Nelson Rockefeller, governor of New York from 1959 to 1974 and Vice President under President Gerald Ford in 1974–1977. Before Rockefeller, Tom Dewey, governor of New York (1942–1954) and <b>GOP</b> <b>presidential</b> nominee in 1944 and 1948 was the leader. Dwight Eisenhower and his aide Henry Cabot Lodge, Jr. reflected many of their views.|$|E
