50|$|In 1968, Nixon {{and native}} Southerner and American Independent {{candidate}} George Wallace carried {{the same number}} of states in the South. With Nixon's reelection and sweep of the South—as well as nearly every state in the country—in 1972, the Democratic stronghold of the Solid South had fallen to the <b>GOP</b> at the <b>presidential</b> level, save for 1976, 1992, and 1996. However state and local elections were still dominated by Democrats until the 1990s.|$|R
